        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-08 16:27:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe problem you're seeing is that you need to have separate commits for the release of Gerrit artifacts (3.2.0.yaml) and the release of dockers (3.2.0-container.yaml).  Unfortunately the verify build doesn't catch this, but the merge build will fail if it finds both.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "540bbefec20145725b8cf523065ff4fe1b65950b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 87,
          "name": "Dan Timoney",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dtimoney@att.com",
          "username": "djtimoney"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-08 16:29:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> The problem you're seeing is that you need to have separate commits for the release of Gerrit artifacts (3.2.0.yaml) and the release of dockers (3.2.0-container.yaml).  Unfortunately the verify build doesn't catch this, but the merge build will fail if it finds both.\n\nProbably the best way to deal with this is create 3 new updates:\n\n1) Remove both these files (git rm).\n2) Add back just 3.2.0.yaml\n3) Add back 3.2.0-container.yaml\n\nAlso, be sure to wait for the merge build for the 3.2.0.yaml to finish before merging the 3.2.0-container.yaml change - otherwise, the second merge build will fail.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      }
    ]
